
/*
 * Sets the value of the [.has-sent-waiting] node to true, indicating that a certain condition or state has been met or changed to true. This is useful for flagging or marking a specific state within a Hyperlambda execution. 
 * 
 * 1. [set-value] - Changes the value of the specified node.
 * 2. [.:bool:true] - The new value to set, which is a boolean true.
 */
set-value:x:@.has-sent-waiting
   .:bool:true
